Dhaka stocks end down as blue chips fall . Dhaka stocks closed down on Sunday amid profit taking on blue chip shares by retail investors , said brokers . The Dhaka Stock Exchange ( DSE ) all - share price index fell 40 . 87 points or 2 . 29 percent at 1 , 740 . 86 on a turnover of 106 . 4 million taka . Of 123 traded issues 17 gained and 100 lost and six unchanged . Leasing company IDLC lost 98 taka to 4 , 912 , Atlas Bangladesh shed 447 to 377 and Bangladesh Oxyzen was down 5 . 0 to 230 . ( ( - - Dhaka Newsroom + 880 - 2 - 506363 ) ) 
